Building a New Race
-------------------

These are the technical stages to making a new race.

1) Add an RCOLOR for the specific race being added and an RACE_MAP entry.

2) Assign racial power pts (100 for common races, 125 for exotic) according
   to the cost guide below. Make sure you add an rbit key linking the race
   to its major race grouping.

3) Set up guild restrictions in guildd.h

4) Write a description for the race and put it in /public/docs/race. The name
   of the file should be the same as your race name, but with underscores
   replacing the spaces. (e.g. the "ice ogre" race has the description
   file /public/docs/race/ice_ogre. For common races, update /public/docs/helpdir/race
   and /public/docs/helpdir/races appropriately. Exotic races should not do this.
   Copy the race description file to /public/docs/helpdir as well for common races.

5) If the race is a common race, add it to one of the continent race rooms.
   (add it to the array passed to set_available_races()), and adjusting
   the room's long desc slightly. If it's exotic make a race room for it.
   To do this, inherit RACE_ROOM instead of ROOM and add:
   
       set_available_races( ({ "race name" }) );
       
   (replacing "race name" with the name of your race).


