                                            (max 3)

SIZE EFFECTS
------------
SMALL  - weapon size effects rise 1 level:
           - cannot use huge weapons
           - all large weapons require 2 hands
           - can only use 1 medium weapon if dual wielding
           - should affect guild weapon restrictions
       - armor size effects [if/when armor sizes are implemented]
LARGE  - weapon size effects drop 1 level:
           - cannot use small weapons
           - if dual wielding, can use 2 large weapons, or 1 huge + 1 large
           - can wield huge weapons in 1 hand unless explicitly 2 handed,
             polearm, or missiles
           - should affect guild weapon restrictions
       - armor size effects [if/when armor sizes are implemented]

STAT ADJUSTMENTS
----------------
- increases/decreases based on the base stats of the player.
- NB extra costs for having high net stat bonuses are in addition to
  the costs of the stat bonuses themselves.

ALIGNMENT TENDENCY
------------------
- increase positive (tendency direction) change by %
- reduce negative change by %
- 1% resistance to related damtype
- -1% resistance to opposite damtype
- use al_law with a negative value for chaotic
- use al_good with negative value for evil
- n.b. tendencies to either direction should be costed positively.

EAT/DRINK
----------------
- increased detox/desate by %
- increased capacity by %
- no change in food/drink size

DAMAGE RESISTANCE/VULNERABILITY
-------------------------------
- the value field of the resistances key is a mapping of the form:
  TYPE:VALUE, where TYPE is a damage type and VALUE is the amount of
  resistance. A negative VALUE is a vulnerability to the damage type.
  
WEAPON MASTERY
--------------
- no penalty for out-of-spec weapon use

HYPERBOREAN
-----------
- +10 resist cold
- -10 resist fire
- +1 resist environmental cold

SOUVRAELI
---------
- +10 resist fire
- -10 resist cold
- +2 resist environmental heat dam

WINGED
------
- allows wing tattoos

FLIGHT
------
- allows flight

RACECHANGE
----------
- allows free race changes 

BREATH
------
- allows special draconian breath spell

SP REGEN RATE
-------------
- increases the base regen rate for sp

LANGUAGES
---------
- array of fluent languages
- first element in array is the native language
- all others count towards total knowable languages

